One File Only : Compress
gzip -c filename > filename.gz

One File Only : Decompress
gzip -d filename.gz
gunzip -d filename.gz

Multiple Files : Compress
tar -zcvf outputted_filename.tgz inputted_filename
* -z = gzip, -c = create, -v = verbose, -f = outputted_filename.tgz (or .tar.gz)
* This will tar (take multiple objects) and compress them into one file
* outputted_filename can be .tgz or .tar.gz

Multiple Files: Decompress
tar -zxvf inputted_filename.tgz
* -z = gzip, -x = extract, -v = verbose, -f = inputted_filename.tgz (or .tar.gz)
